props.name: servingSize

props.name: additionalType
props.desc: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label should follow the schema.org style guide.

props.name: alternateName
props.desc: An alias for the item.

props.name: description
props.desc: A description of the item.

props.name: disambiguatingDescription
props.desc: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

props.name: identifier
props.desc: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.

props.name: image
props.desc: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

props.name: mainEntityOfPage
props.desc:
Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See background notes for details.
Inverse property: mainEntity

props.name: name
props.desc: The name of the item.

props.name: potentialAction
props.desc: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

props.name: sameAs
props.desc: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

props.name: subjectOf
props.desc:
A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.
Inverse property: about

props.name: url
props.desc: URL of the item.
